indexOf

public static <T> int indexOf(T itemToFind,
                              Iterable<T> iterable)
Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified element in this iterable, or -1 if this iterable does not contain the element. More formally, returns the lowest index i such that (o==null ? get(i)==null : o.equals(get(i))), or -1 if there is no such index.
